data.title: What is Albuquerque's "War Zone" and why is it call that way?
data.meta_description: Answer (1 of 15): It is an area predominantly along Central Avenue between San Mateo and Wyoming Ave. where fighting, drug dealing, prostitution and panhandling are dominant among the population. It has been gradually improving. Taking years, the improvement is very slow and sometimes takes a hug...
